A denoising upscale pass (aka HiRes fix) naturally introduces changes to an image, but what and were can sometimes be difficult to identify. Used this way the difference node is a simple and cmputationally efficient means of identify where and to what extent changes have been made.

Why not try experiment with different denoise levels?

Upscaling is an area with an enormous posibility space of settings, methods and models to explore. Some changes you make can be subtle or hard to spot. The difference node can highlight the specific areas of difference so you don't have to play Spot The Difference.

Many of these settings and options equally apply to base generations. The possibilities are endless.

nodes.title: Comparing differences between Input to Output differences

widgets_values:
The image difference node calculates the simple pixel-wise difference between two identically sized images and outputs a visual representation of that difference. Here the difference is created by the mosaic effect node.

You can try out different tile_sizes.

Note that the Mean Square Error value is printed to console as a percentage (0% = identical images, 100% = absolute difference, i.e. one black one white). This can de disabled by toggling console_mse to false.

Contrast Boost increases contrast by a factor of 5 for subtle, hard to spot differences.
